# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Code2Py frontend application following the latest official Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart).

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Package version: Latest available from npm registry

### 2. Configuration
**Modified: frontend/src/App.tsx**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level of the App component
- Placed after the Routes component to ensure tracking is active across all pages

### 3. Files Updated
- `frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `frontend/package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and dependencies
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` - Configured Analytics component

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was placed in the App.tsx file, which is the root application component. This ensures that:
- Analytics tracking works across all routes (Landing, Analyze, Dashboard, Login, Notes, Learning Path)
- The component is initialized once when the app loads
- Page view tracking is automatically handled by Vercel Analytics

## Framework: React + Vite
This project uses React 19.2.7 with Vite 8.1.0 as the build tool. The Analytics implementation follows the React-specific integration pattern from Vercel's official documentation.

## Testing & Verification

✅ **Build Verification**: Successfully ran `npm run build` - project compiles without errors
✅ **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` - no new errors introduced (only pre-existing warnings remain)
✅ **Dependencies**: package-lock.json properly updated with all new dependencies

## Next Steps (To Be Done by User)

To activate analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics → Enable)
3. Once deployed, analytics will automatically start tracking page views and user interactions

## Technical Notes

- The Analytics component is lightweight and has no visual UI
- It automatically tracks page views using the browser's navigation API
- Data collection is GDPR compliant and respects user privacy settings
- The component works seamlessly with React Router for SPA navigation
